==English==
===Etymology===
John Norton, an early wowser (temperance sense), claimed it to be an [[acronym]] for "We Only Want Social Evils Remedied", but that's likely to have been a back-formation.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# {{AU}} {{NZ}} A person with a strong [[moral]] views for [[temperance]], [[abstinence]], etc, and who promotes them generally or in particular seeks to [[impose]] them on other people. [http://www.anu.edu.au/andc/ozwords/May_97/4._aussie_words.htm]
# {{obsolete}} A [[lout]] or similar disruptive person.